==Latin==
In Latin, the letter U is a modern typographical convention for the [[vowel]] form of [[V]].  The letter V in ancient times denoted either a vowel or a consonant, see [[V#Latin|V]] for more information.

===Pronunciation===
* Classical: IPA: short /u/, long /u:/

